    en: "The New York State Freelance Isn't Free Act (FIFA) took effect on August 28, 2024. Under General Business Law Article 44-A, any business that hires a freelance worker for $800 or more in any 120-day period has to provide a written contract, pay on time, and keep a copy of the contract for six years. Late or missing payment exposes the business to double damages plus attorney's fees. Retaliation against a freelancer who complains is a separate violation. The NYS Attorney General's Labor Bureau enforces the law, and a freelancer can also file a civil lawsuit."
